ism offers a theory of revolutionary cooptation that, in part, selectively employs practices and strategies of the dominant order to radically alter the coordinates of power and possibility. Underscoring the potential, vitality, and power of emerging democratic practices to change the world, Visionary Pragmatism's simultaneous theoretical rigor and grounding in actual political and ecological practices provokes and inspires new ways of cocreating knowledge and action in dark times.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aCapitalismxEnvironmental aspectszUnited States. 0aCapitalismxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aCommunity organizationzUnited States. 0aDemocracyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aDemocracyzUnited StatesxCitizen participation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374664zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374664423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374664.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles